cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The use of local structure analysis and multiscale filtering also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The approach also involves learning a set of kernels, which suggests that it may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of filtering and blending techniques may suggest that it belongs to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
